==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Riddance
<hw>Rid"dance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of ridding or freeing; deliverance; a cleaning up or out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou shalt not make clean <qex>riddance</qex> of the corners of
thy field.</q> <rj><qau>Lev. xxiii. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being rid or free; freedom;
escape.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Riddance</xex> from all adversity.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ridden</ent>⟦br⟧
